MPs will be recalled next week to approve the new IEBC and EACC commissioners.National Assembly Speaker Justin Muturi has reconvened a special sitting next Tuesday to consider JLAC&rsquo;s report to pave way for appointment of the commissioners by President Uhuru Kenyatta before their swearing in.The Justice and Legal Affairs Committee will table the two reports during the special sitting and MPs are expected to approve the nominees.The key House legal panel which has been vetting nominees for the IEBC for two days will retreat today to write its report. &ldquo;We hope the House will approve the nominees so that they can take charge of the IEBC from the current commissioners,&rdquo; JLAC chairman Samuel Chepkong&rsquo;a said.